Product Description With a unique, embossed super absorbent polymer core, Ultrasorbs are premium pads engineered to absorb 10 times more liquid than typical underpads. That helps lock in moisture and odors, keeping bedding and other surfaces dry, clean and comfortable. The quilted core is made to stay flat and won’t bunch, swell or wrinkle when it absorbs moisture. Non-slippery, leak-proof backing feels like regular fabric and keeps liquids from seeping through. Safe and gentle, our Ultrasorbs are proven, hospital-grade pads made from 100% latex-free, non-woven material, without any irritating chemicals or scents. They’re great for everyone from infants to the elderly, including those with sensitive skin. Wetness and bacteria due to incontinence can raise the risk of skin damage, incontinence-associated dermatitis (IAD), infection and other skin issues, so the moisture wicking advantages of Ultrasorbs help keep skin dry and protected. They’re also versatile, practical and perfect many uses around the house. Use them like medical facilities for protection from incontinence, after having a baby, or after surgery. They also make great disposable pee pads for children in the potty-training stage. Let Medline Disposable Ultrasorbs Drypads give you peace of mind while protecting not just your possessions, but the people you care about. From the Manufacturer With a unique, embossed super absorbent polymer core, Ultrasorbs are premium pads engineered to absorb 10 times more liquid than typical underpads. That helps lock in moisture and odors, keeping bedding and other surfaces dry, clean and comfortable. The quilted core is made to stay flat and won’t bunch, swell or wrinkle when it absorbs moisture. Non-slippery, leak-proof backing feels like regular fabric and keeps liquids from seeping through. Safe and gentle, our Ultrasorbs are proven, hospital-grade pads made from 100% latex-free, non-woven material, without any irritating chemicals or scents. They’re great for everyo